description.narrative: Significant improvement made on increasing access and delivery of quality and more specialized Maternal and Newborn Care services in the UNICEF supported regions. High impact interventions and integrated approaches adopted at facility and community levels led to increased utilization of quality and safe RMNCAH services in the focus regions. On immunization services with countrywide support from UNICEF, DPT3 coverage remained higher and above target where 98% of the targeted children were reached and received. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2019
